            <section ID="i4i_description_id_4fac1b55-e32d-4fd9-9570-b2f69188de1d">
               <id root="7a589658-49e3-4a80-8e2b-435c66fa31d2"/>
               <code codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" code="34089-3" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Methimazole (1-methylimidazole-2-thiol) is a white, crystalline substance that is freely soluble in water. It differs chemically from the drugs of the thiouracil series primarily because it has a 5- instead of a 6-membered ring.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Each tablet contains 5 or 10 mg (43.8 or 87.6 μmol) methimazole, an orally administered antithyroid drug. Each tablet also contains lactose monohydrate, magnesium stearate, corn starch, and talc.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>The molecular weight is 114.17, and the molecular formula is C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>6</sub>N<sub>2</sub>S. The structural formula is as follows:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="id_d108a006-e720-41e3-8377-14711fd9da77"/>
                  </paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20130925"/>
               <component>
                  <observationMedia ID="id_d108a006-e720-41e3-8377-14711fd9da77">
                     <text>Methimazole Structural Formula</text>
